# PurchaseIQ — Python Recommendation Engine

## Setup & Run

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
```

Open http://localhost:5000 in your browser.

## Project Structure

```
app.py           ← Flask server + Python CF engine
static/
  index.html     ← Frontend UI
requirements.txt
```

## CSV Format

```
user_id,ProductA,ProductB,ProductC
Alice,1,0,1
Bob,0,1,1
```

- First column: `user_id`
- Remaining columns: product names
- Values: `1` = purchased, `0` = not purchased (also supports ratings 1–5)

## Algorithm

1. `pd.read_csv()` — parse uploaded file into DataFrame
2. Mean-fill zeros per user (bias correction)
3. `cosine_similarity()` — compute pairwise user similarity (scikit-learn)
4. Top-K peer users selected per user (K=10)
5. Score unseen items by averaging peer ratings
6. Return top-N ranked recommendations per user (N=8)